field_paragraph_text.value:
Use your Notebook to respond to the following questions for your SWOT Analysis:

 

To find your strengths, think about:

  • Why is your project better than other projects?
  • What can your team do well?

 

To find your weaknesses, think about:

  • What are some things you could improve in your project or in your team?
  • What are some things your team has a hard time doing?

 

To find your opportunities, think about:

  • What is happening in your community or country that could help this project?
  • Are there other people or organizations that could help with some part of this project or may be interested in your work?
  • What is the niche, the particular thing that this project will do so well that others can’t do?

 

To find your threats, think about:

  • What are some things happening in your community or country that could harm your project that you do not have control over?
  • What is the competition for this project? Are there others doing this same or similar work? If there is no competition, explain it.
